WEBVTT

00:06.000 --> 00:08.125
♪ ♪

00:09.250 --> 00:10.916
[gasping]

00:17.625 --> 00:19.625
♪ ♪

00:31.750 --> 00:33.625
[mutters]

00:33.666 --> 00:34.791
[vehicle door closes]

00:42.416 --> 00:45.125
[Cecilia] Tell me you did not
drive through my gate.

00:45.208 --> 00:46.958
Tell me that, please.
I heard what's been going on.

00:47.041 --> 00:48.333
You've lost your damn minds.

00:48.416 --> 00:50.875
Good God, look at you, Billy.
You're a mess.

00:50.958 --> 00:53.541
- Just hand on a second...
- Boys, come on now.
It's late and you're drunk.

00:53.625 --> 00:55.375
And before you do anything
else stupid, I think you ought

00:55.458 --> 00:57.416
to just go home and wait for
your brother there, all right?

00:57.500 --> 00:59.666
- Where's Rhett and Perry? I...
- I don't want to hear it!

00:59.750 --> 01:01.250
Now go home and cool off.
I can't believe

01:01.333 --> 01:02.500
I haven't even heard
an apology yet.

01:02.583 --> 01:03.958
- Sorry, Mrs. Abbott.
- Thank you, Billy.

01:04.000 --> 01:05.250
See, Luke? Be smart.

01:05.375 --> 01:06.708
Follow your brother's lead here,
and we'll talk later.

01:06.750 --> 01:07.875
Okay? Good night. God bless.

01:24.208 --> 01:28.375
[sighs] All right.
Where's your father?

01:32.708 --> 01:34.625
♪ ♪

01:49.083 --> 01:51.083
[thunder rumbling]

02:03.166 --> 02:05.125
[grunting]

02:23.791 --> 02:25.833
♪ ♪

02:27.583 --> 02:29.416
- [thunder rumbling]
- [gasps]

02:29.458 --> 02:33.125
[groaning]

02:40.041 --> 02:42.000
♪ ♪

02:50.541 --> 02:52.625
[panting]

02:52.708 --> 02:54.708
[horse neighs]

03:04.333 --> 03:06.000
[horse snorts]

03:10.041 --> 03:12.041
♪ ♪

03:21.750 --> 03:23.291
[door opens]

03:23.375 --> 03:25.375
[footsteps approaching]

03:26.583 --> 03:28.375
[door closes]

03:35.333 --> 03:37.125
I'm-a go get a shirt.

04:00.583 --> 04:01.916
[Cecilia] What happened
to your leg?

04:02.000 --> 04:03.541
Don't worry about that.

04:03.625 --> 04:05.541
- [Rhett] You're bleeding.
- I'm fine.

04:07.208 --> 04:09.541
All right, then.
Where's the body?

04:09.625 --> 04:11.666
[Rhett] Don't tell me that.
I don't want to know that.

04:11.750 --> 04:14.291
If this all goes to shit,
it's on me, too, pal.

04:14.375 --> 04:16.000
If it does come to that,
I'm taking all the blame.

04:16.125 --> 04:18.250
Perry, stop.

04:18.333 --> 04:20.250
We are all in this.

04:23.916 --> 04:26.625
Okay, Royal, look...

04:26.708 --> 04:30.625
you tell us everything
you think we need to know.

04:33.333 --> 04:35.375
It's gone.

04:35.458 --> 04:37.541
The body's gone.
That's all there is to know.

04:37.625 --> 04:39.250
- [Perry] Is it on our land?
- It's gone.

04:41.875 --> 04:43.208
So, what's next?

04:43.291 --> 04:44.666
We get back to work,
that's what's next.

04:44.750 --> 04:47.166
- [Perry] Dad.
- This ranch needs to be
business as usual.

04:47.250 --> 04:48.541
So, what, just act like
all this never happened?

04:48.625 --> 04:50.625
You want to tell me
what else there is to do?

04:50.708 --> 04:52.625
[Rhett] Well, first off,
there's that woman on our land.

04:52.708 --> 04:55.250
What woman?
What woman, Royal?

04:55.333 --> 04:57.625
[Rhett] There's a hippie chick
camping on the west pasture.

04:57.708 --> 04:59.625
- [Cecilia] Since when?
- Since recently.
- [Rhett] Since last week.

04:59.708 --> 05:01.166
- Jesus Christ.
- [Cecilia] When were you gonna
tell me about this?

05:01.250 --> 05:02.500
- [Royal] Look...
- If she saw something...

05:02.583 --> 05:03.791
- [Royal] She didn't.
- How do you know that?

05:03.875 --> 05:05.500
I need you all to trust me.

05:05.583 --> 05:08.166
- Is she still out there?
- N-No. I'll find her.

05:08.250 --> 05:09.541
You get her off this land
as soon as possible.

05:09.625 --> 05:10.875
But hold on, we need to know

05:10.958 --> 05:12.041
if she saw something.

05:12.125 --> 05:13.500
We need to find her,
talk to her.

05:13.583 --> 05:15.541
I'll find her, okay?
I'll figure it out.

05:15.625 --> 05:16.958
Yeah, you done better had, pal.

05:17.041 --> 05:18.625
[Perry] What about traces
of anything else?

05:18.708 --> 05:20.583
- Like what?
- [Cecilia] Like your shirt.
Oh, my God.

05:20.666 --> 05:22.750
- [overlapping chatter]
- I told you I don't know
where my shirt is.

05:22.833 --> 05:24.000
[Rhett] You sure about that?

05:24.083 --> 05:25.333
What do you mean,
am I sure about that?

05:25.416 --> 05:26.916
Do not get snippy
with your father.

05:27.000 --> 05:28.708
If you're asking us
to go all in on this,

05:28.791 --> 05:30.750
then we got to be
on the same page.

05:30.833 --> 05:32.458
What are you talking about?

05:35.250 --> 05:37.958
Your-your leg's bleeding.

05:38.041 --> 05:40.958
Well, I'm all right, hon.

05:41.041 --> 05:42.791
[Amy] Why is his leg bleeding?

05:43.833 --> 05:46.041
Amy, could you give us a minute?

05:46.125 --> 05:49.541
- [Cecilia] Look, hon...
- I have to eat breakfast
before I go to school.

05:57.833 --> 06:00.333
[Cecilia sighs]

06:00.416 --> 06:03.000
♪ ♪

06:03.083 --> 06:04.875
Was it Luke or Billy?

06:04.958 --> 06:07.083
- Huh?
- That shot you.

06:10.125 --> 06:11.625
Mm, it was Luke.

06:14.458 --> 06:16.125
But you're telling me
he didn't see you?

06:16.208 --> 06:18.708
No. Got lucky.

06:18.791 --> 06:21.166
Fired one off in the dark.

06:27.666 --> 06:30.000
You think we'll be forgiven
for this?

06:31.833 --> 06:34.000
Fixing to find out.

06:38.375 --> 06:40.625
- [♪ Supertramp:
"Goodbye Stranger"]
- ♪ Goodbye Jane ♪

06:40.708 --> 06:42.166
[Joy] Rose, honey,
eat your breakfast.

06:42.208 --> 06:43.333
♪ Meet again... ♪

06:43.416 --> 06:44.708
Who on earth keeps dinging you?

06:44.791 --> 06:47.208
Luke Tillerson,
asking if we've seen Trevor.

06:47.291 --> 06:48.666
Mm.

06:49.666 --> 06:51.416
Should've never given
that family my cell.

06:51.500 --> 06:53.333
- ♪ Sweet devotion ♪
- ♪ Goodbye Mary ♪

06:53.416 --> 06:55.208
- ♪ It's not for me ♪
- ♪ Goodbye Jane ♪

06:55.291 --> 06:57.041
- ♪ Just give me motion ♪
- ♪ Will we ever ♪

06:57.125 --> 06:59.125
- ♪ To set me free ♪
- ♪ Meet again ♪

06:59.208 --> 07:01.166
- ♪ In the land and the ocean ♪
- ♪ Feel no sorrow ♪

07:01.250 --> 07:02.375
♪ Far away ♪

07:02.458 --> 07:03.791
- ♪ Feel no shame ♪
- [horn honks]

07:03.875 --> 07:05.375
[Joy] Attaboy, Fred!

07:05.458 --> 07:06.958
♪ Feel no pain ♪

07:07.041 --> 07:08.541
- ♪ So goodbye Mary ♪
- ♪ Goodbye Mary ♪

07:08.625 --> 07:10.500
- ♪ So goodbye Jane ♪
- ♪ Goodbye Jane ♪

07:10.583 --> 07:12.416
- ♪ Will we ever ♪
- ♪ Will we ever ♪

07:12.500 --> 07:14.208
- Eff me, that's hot.
- ♪ Meet again ♪

07:14.291 --> 07:16.708
♪ Meet again ♪♪

07:28.833 --> 07:31.083
Hey, Rhett, how you doing?

07:31.166 --> 07:32.833
Sheriff Joy.

07:32.875 --> 07:34.250
[horse snorts]

07:39.041 --> 07:40.791
Shit.

07:40.875 --> 07:42.500
- Come on. [smacks lips]
- [horse whinnies]

07:45.750 --> 07:46.791
[Joy] It's a buckle.

07:46.875 --> 07:48.375
[Luke] It's Trevor's.

07:48.458 --> 07:51.041
Found it behind the roadhouse
the last night we saw him.

07:51.125 --> 07:52.291
All right.

07:52.375 --> 07:54.000
- And that was when?
- Sunday.

07:55.833 --> 07:57.083
What do you want me to do
with this?

07:57.166 --> 07:59.375
Investigate.

07:59.458 --> 08:01.416
Look, there's blood right there.

08:01.500 --> 08:03.750
You know damn well
that could be anything.

08:03.833 --> 08:06.291
- And as sheriff, I can't...
- Acting sheriff.

08:07.291 --> 08:09.083
Sorry, that's just... that's
your official title, right?

08:09.166 --> 08:10.291
Since Burt died?

08:10.375 --> 08:12.333
Yeah. The point is,

08:12.416 --> 08:14.416
I can't admit this as evidence,
Luke, you just handed it to me.

08:14.500 --> 08:16.000
[chuckles softly]

08:16.083 --> 08:17.833
I get that you're worried,

08:17.916 --> 08:19.583
but would I be right in assuming
this ain't the first time

08:19.666 --> 08:21.708
Trev's gone missing
for a day or two?

08:21.791 --> 08:23.041
Trust me.

08:23.125 --> 08:24.875
We'll keep our eye on it.

08:27.250 --> 08:28.416
[scoffs]

08:30.333 --> 08:33.791
I hear you're running
against Trudy Cole for sheriff.

08:33.875 --> 08:36.416
[chuckles] I'd say
he's running against me.

08:36.500 --> 08:38.583
That guy's got some fans
in Lander.

08:38.666 --> 08:40.250
Should be a good race.

08:40.333 --> 08:41.916
- Mm.
- [snaps fingers]

08:42.000 --> 08:44.583
- When's the vote?
- 28 days.

08:44.666 --> 08:46.458
[Luke whistles]

08:50.041 --> 08:51.958
Never been an Indian sheriff
before.

08:52.041 --> 08:54.000
Or a gay one. [chuckles]

08:55.208 --> 08:58.291
Well, it's about time.

08:58.375 --> 08:59.833
Why don't you let us know
how we can help?

09:00.875 --> 09:04.000
And, uh, I'm sorry to bother you
about this Trevor stuff.

09:04.083 --> 09:06.541
You know, we're just
real worried about him,

09:06.625 --> 09:08.333
that's all.

09:10.375 --> 09:11.583
I tell you what.

09:11.666 --> 09:13.958
Let me bring this
down to the office.

09:14.041 --> 09:16.166
You mind if I take this with me?

09:16.250 --> 09:18.625
No. It's all yours.

09:18.708 --> 09:20.708
♪ ♪

09:46.750 --> 09:48.750
♪ ♪

10:07.458 --> 10:09.458
[music playing softly
over radio]

10:20.125 --> 10:23.708
- Hi.
- Hi.

10:23.791 --> 10:26.750
Is there any change we can chat
somewhere else?

10:26.833 --> 10:30.333
Uh... I don't know. I don't have
a break for another hour.

10:30.416 --> 10:31.958
Okay.

10:32.041 --> 10:33.583
Okay what?

10:34.625 --> 10:35.958
I'll wait.

10:36.958 --> 10:38.916
Here? At the bank?

10:39.000 --> 10:40.333
- Yeah, or, you know, wherever.
- [chuckles]

10:40.416 --> 10:42.500
Meet me at the diner
across the street.

10:43.583 --> 10:44.833
Okay.

10:48.958 --> 10:51.291
[Rhett] That was it,

10:51.375 --> 10:53.208
until I saw my dad
win the rodeo.

10:55.125 --> 10:56.833
Ever since then, I knew.

10:56.916 --> 10:58.750
Didn't want to do anything
but ride bulls.

10:58.833 --> 11:00.416
Congratulations, by the way.

11:00.500 --> 11:03.125
- On what?
- On moving forward.

11:03.208 --> 11:07.166
The guy that placed higher
than you was DQ'd for drugs.

11:07.250 --> 11:08.666
You're riding next week.

11:09.708 --> 11:12.166
[stammers quietly] What?

11:12.250 --> 11:13.583
- Are you serious?
- [chuckles]

11:13.666 --> 11:15.416
Been on another planet
or something?

11:17.833 --> 11:20.625
No, uh, um...

11:20.708 --> 11:23.416
Just been a lot going on.

11:29.916 --> 11:31.541
Hey, do you want
to get dinner with me?

11:31.625 --> 11:35.958
- Um...
- I mean, not tonight.
Just whenever.

11:36.041 --> 11:38.916
- Or tonight,
if you want to tonight.
- Wait, are you asking me out?

11:40.000 --> 11:42.666
- Sí. Yeah.
- Oh, you speak Spanish now?

11:42.750 --> 11:44.791
- [chuckles]
- Pero es sólo poquito.

11:44.875 --> 11:46.875
Mm.

11:46.958 --> 11:48.333
Está bien.

11:48.416 --> 11:49.958
Voy ir a cenar contigo.

11:50.041 --> 11:52.916
Pero te advierto que usualmente
no salgo con güeros como tú.

11:53.000 --> 11:55.166
Vas a tender que echarle
muchos huevos.

11:55.250 --> 11:57.291
¿Entendiste?

11:59.541 --> 12:01.916
- I didn't understand that
at all...
- [chuckles]

12:02.000 --> 12:04.375
...but, um, how about...
how about tomorrow?

12:04.458 --> 12:07.875
Yeah. Tomorrow works.

12:09.333 --> 12:12.333
Is that what
you wanted to talk about?

12:12.416 --> 12:13.791
No, it was something else.

12:13.875 --> 12:15.458
The other night,

12:15.541 --> 12:18.041
I'm not too proud
of what I did to Trevor.

12:18.125 --> 12:20.541
You mean the fight?
It's all right.

12:20.625 --> 12:22.791
I never liked that guy much,
anyway.

12:22.875 --> 12:23.875
No, it's just...

12:23.958 --> 12:26.416
Well, you know the Tillersons.

12:27.666 --> 12:31.250
If you wouldn't mind,
keep that quiet.

12:32.291 --> 12:34.125
You got it.

12:34.208 --> 12:36.208
[phone ringing faintly]

12:47.583 --> 12:49.375
- [phone beeps]
- Hello?

12:52.458 --> 12:55.166
[cattle lowing]

12:55.250 --> 12:58.291
[Cecilia] Hey. 600 acres?

12:58.375 --> 13:00.916
Some snake of a lawyer
for the Tillersons

13:01.000 --> 13:03.000
- just called and told me.
- I know. I know.

13:03.083 --> 13:04.958
Well, why is this
the first I'm hearing about it?

13:05.041 --> 13:06.458
A lot's been going on
around here,

13:06.541 --> 13:08.541
in case you haven't noticed.
We got bigger fish to fry.

13:08.625 --> 13:10.250
Oh, I'd say half
our west pasture is

13:10.333 --> 13:12.208
a pretty damn big fish.

13:13.541 --> 13:14.625
Where are you going?

13:14.708 --> 13:16.208
Go see Todd Barney.

13:18.708 --> 13:21.041
Hey, hey. Take Perry with you.

13:21.125 --> 13:22.708
No, he's got to work.

13:22.791 --> 13:24.541
No, what he needs is his father.

13:24.625 --> 13:27.000
Now, I-I don't know
if he can shake this, Royal.

13:27.083 --> 13:29.208
Please, just try and help him.

13:29.291 --> 13:30.500
Can't bear to see him like this.

13:30.583 --> 13:32.541
- All right.
- Okay.

13:39.083 --> 13:40.916
It was an accident.

13:42.041 --> 13:43.333
Both of you were drunk.

13:43.416 --> 13:45.458
Got in a fight. Went too far.

13:48.000 --> 13:50.083
It was an accident, right?

13:54.083 --> 13:56.833
I stopped believing
in accidents.

14:02.041 --> 14:04.541
You talking about Rebecca?

14:05.541 --> 14:08.208
I'm talking about fate.

14:08.291 --> 14:10.708
Fate.

14:10.791 --> 14:12.666
[Perry] Yeah.

14:12.750 --> 14:14.250
What about it?

14:14.333 --> 14:17.750
Is that how you think
the world works?

14:19.125 --> 14:21.125
[Royal exhales slowly]

14:26.291 --> 14:29.291
I don't know
how the world works.

14:34.375 --> 14:35.666
[Todd] So this here's
your ranch.

14:35.750 --> 14:37.583
Rights assigned in 1878.

14:37.666 --> 14:38.916
And this here is
the Tillerson ranch.

14:39.000 --> 14:41.375
Right assigned in 1872.

14:41.458 --> 14:43.791
Now, these honeyfugglers claim
you're 600 acres

14:43.875 --> 14:46.375
onto their land,
and here's why.

14:46.458 --> 14:48.416
State had all sorts of issues

14:48.500 --> 14:50.625
when they restructured
country lines,

14:50.708 --> 14:52.333
so what you got here is
a good old-fashioned

14:52.416 --> 14:53.750
topographical fuck job.

14:53.833 --> 14:55.458
See that?

14:55.541 --> 14:57.083
That's a corner
of your west pasture.

14:57.166 --> 14:58.583
But by this map,
you can't tell

14:58.666 --> 15:00.416
if it's Tillerson land
or no one's land.

15:00.500 --> 15:01.833
It's all higgledy-piggledy.

15:01.916 --> 15:05.583
Point is, they got a hell of
a case it ain't yours.

15:05.666 --> 15:07.958
Or what, they got a county
assessor in their pocket?

15:08.041 --> 15:10.541
- Certainly possible.
- Mm.

15:10.625 --> 15:12.125
You want my advice?

15:12.208 --> 15:13.958
- Give them the damn land.
- No.

15:14.041 --> 15:16.166
It's pretty country,
but it ain't worth losing

15:16.250 --> 15:19.333
- the whole ranch over.
- All right,
let me get this straight, Todd.

15:19.416 --> 15:22.875
My own lawyer's advice is
just to go chickenshit on this

15:22.958 --> 15:25.375
and hand over a mile
of our own property?

15:25.458 --> 15:27.333
This ain't just any piece
of land we're talking about.

15:27.416 --> 15:29.958
It's where our family ranched
for three generations.

15:31.458 --> 15:33.375
I'm not just gonna up
and give it away.

15:33.458 --> 15:37.958
- All I'm saying is,
the Tillersons don't lose.
- Yeah.

15:38.041 --> 15:40.708
A first for everything, Todd.

15:44.666 --> 15:45.916
Oof.

15:46.000 --> 15:48.041
[Perry] Look, he's got a point.

15:48.125 --> 15:49.375
We give them the acreage,

15:49.458 --> 15:52.416
maybe they'll back off
the Trevor stuff.

15:52.500 --> 15:54.666
Why not cozy up to them,
get them off our backs?

15:54.750 --> 15:59.083
Son, let me tell you
about the Tillersons, okay?

15:59.166 --> 16:00.791
Look, when you were a kid,

16:00.875 --> 16:03.375
Wayne Tillerson had a ranch hand
that was gored by a bull.

16:03.458 --> 16:06.125
Stuck clean through the stomach.

16:06.208 --> 16:08.250
Everyone knew he was done for,
but no one could get him

16:08.333 --> 16:10.166
free of the animal.

16:10.250 --> 16:12.541
So, with the ambulance, like,
an hour away,

16:12.625 --> 16:14.666
Wayne had two choices:

16:14.750 --> 16:16.791
shoot the bull,
killing valuable stock

16:16.875 --> 16:18.791
but giving the man
a dignified death,

16:18.875 --> 16:20.791
or don't.

16:20.875 --> 16:23.041
Wayne chose the second one.

16:23.125 --> 16:25.166
Sent everyone back to work
as the guy dragged around

16:25.250 --> 16:28.541
on that bull before the ranch
hand breathed his last.

16:30.041 --> 16:32.416
You don't cozy up
to the Tillersons.

16:32.500 --> 16:34.333
You keep them as far away
as possible.

16:34.416 --> 16:36.416
♪ ♪

16:42.333 --> 16:44.333
♪ ♪

17:10.125 --> 17:12.583
Something happen to your leg?

17:12.666 --> 17:14.708
Ah, just old age.

17:14.791 --> 17:16.666
Pulled it getting out of bed,

17:16.750 --> 17:18.208
if you can believe it.
[chuckles]

17:25.250 --> 17:27.541
I'll let him know you're here.

17:27.583 --> 17:29.583
[faint voice singing]

17:34.166 --> 17:36.375
[Billy] ♪ ...from myself ♪

17:36.458 --> 17:40.583
♪ There's nowhere to hide ♪

17:40.666 --> 17:45.666
♪ Don't make me close
one more door ♪

17:45.750 --> 17:49.875
♪ I don't want to hurt anymore ♪

17:49.958 --> 17:54.666
♪ Stay in my arms if you dare ♪

17:54.750 --> 17:59.291
♪ Or must I imagine you there? ♪

17:59.375 --> 18:02.583
♪ Don't walk away from me ♪

18:04.291 --> 18:07.666
♪ I have nothing, nothing ♪

18:07.750 --> 18:10.250
♪ Nothing ♪

18:11.375 --> 18:16.250
♪ If I don't have you ♪♪

18:16.333 --> 18:19.583
All right. Come on.

18:23.666 --> 18:25.666
[monitor beeping steadily]

18:29.375 --> 18:31.041
[Luke clears throat]

18:32.750 --> 18:34.750
[bed whirring]

18:48.750 --> 18:49.708
Royal.

18:49.791 --> 18:52.583
Wayne. How's the, uh...

18:52.666 --> 18:55.375
Luke, would you fetch me
a Clamato?

18:55.458 --> 18:57.375
Royal, something to drink?
Clamato?

18:57.458 --> 18:59.500
Uh, you got iced tea?

19:01.375 --> 19:04.000
Oh, same as him. Thanks.

19:07.625 --> 19:10.208
- You still looking for Trev?
- Luke's on it.

19:10.291 --> 19:12.666
I'm sure he's just off
on one of his hellbenders,

19:12.750 --> 19:15.791
or passed out in some biddy's
bed, or blah, blah, blah.

19:15.875 --> 19:18.208
Let's get down to brass tacks,
Roy, you're on my land.

19:18.291 --> 19:21.583
- Now, hold on now.
- Hey, you should be happy
I ain't asking for reparations

19:21.666 --> 19:24.000
- for all the years
you stoled it.
- Now, let's be honest here,

19:24.083 --> 19:25.500
no one's stealing anything
but you.

19:25.583 --> 19:27.041
This is Wyoming, Roy.

19:27.125 --> 19:29.833
It's only ever been stoled
since the day it got its name.

19:29.916 --> 19:31.875
You pay someone off?

19:31.958 --> 19:33.625
[Wayne] Only one person
breaking the law here.

19:33.708 --> 19:35.416
State says it ain't me.

19:35.500 --> 19:36.708
[Royal] Then why now?

19:36.791 --> 19:38.250
Maybe I just want to get
closer to you.

19:38.333 --> 19:39.916
Hmm.

19:42.458 --> 19:44.458
[takes deep breath]

19:46.250 --> 19:48.916
I'll give you 200 acres
of my south pasture instead.

19:49.000 --> 19:50.750
West.

19:50.833 --> 19:52.916
Why west?

19:55.166 --> 19:57.416
Why west, you know?

20:04.583 --> 20:06.333
You tell me.

20:06.416 --> 20:07.958
[footsteps approaching]

20:08.041 --> 20:09.750
You know, there was a period
in the late '80s

20:09.833 --> 20:12.041
when I got really
into erotic art.

20:12.125 --> 20:14.458
I must've bought
three dozen paintings.

20:14.541 --> 20:16.333
You know, I ain't talking about
any prudes, you know.

20:16.416 --> 20:18.125
I'm not talking about
Aubrey Beardsley

20:18.208 --> 20:20.291
or Pablo fucking Picasso.

20:20.375 --> 20:21.833
I'm talking about
the real out-there stuff.

20:21.916 --> 20:23.166
Stomach in your throat
kind of stuff.

20:23.250 --> 20:25.458
Nan Goldin. Betty Tompkins.

20:25.541 --> 20:26.958
George Condo,
you see what I mean?

20:28.166 --> 20:29.625
Ah...

20:29.708 --> 20:31.583
And I did it because I thought
I wanted something spicy,

20:31.666 --> 20:33.875
I thought I wanted
something gooey.

20:33.958 --> 20:38.208
Yeah, I wanted my home
to be a place

20:38.291 --> 20:40.208
where your ticker sped up.

20:42.375 --> 20:45.125
But that didn't happen.

20:46.750 --> 20:49.750
So I bought more and more.

20:49.833 --> 20:52.875
I kept thinking if I could
just find the right painting,

20:52.958 --> 20:57.541
if I could just find
the right photograph, you know?

20:57.625 --> 21:04.708
Pretty soon the walls were
covered in smut,

21:04.791 --> 21:07.958
it would make your toes curl.

21:08.041 --> 21:13.458
And yet, still, it didn't work.

21:15.083 --> 21:18.250
And what I realized...

21:18.333 --> 21:21.208
was that what got
my heart racing

21:21.291 --> 21:24.416
was what I couldn't see,

21:24.500 --> 21:27.666
what I didn't know about.

21:27.750 --> 21:30.583
It was hidden from me

21:30.666 --> 21:32.833
and kept me looking.

21:36.166 --> 21:38.583
We're born to hunt,

21:38.666 --> 21:41.291
and one frontier begets another.

21:43.125 --> 21:45.833
I'm hungry more
than anything else.

21:50.791 --> 21:52.750
Ah...

21:54.958 --> 21:58.291
I want your west pasture
'cause I want your west pasture.

21:58.375 --> 22:00.916
[laughs]

22:03.333 --> 22:05.708
I'm offering you a hell of
a deal on the valley...

22:05.791 --> 22:09.250
I don't care if you're offering
me a second dinger, Roy.

22:09.333 --> 22:11.625
That west pasture is
gonna be mine.

22:11.708 --> 22:14.708
And the goddamn state of Wyoming
says so, too.

22:21.458 --> 22:23.125
[inhales sharply]

22:24.625 --> 22:27.000
I guess we'll have
the lawyers figure it out, then.

22:29.333 --> 22:32.041
What's so special to you
about that land?

22:34.125 --> 22:36.833
I suppose it's just sentimental.

22:36.916 --> 22:40.625
You always were shifty.

22:40.708 --> 22:44.541
Ever since the day we met.

22:45.541 --> 22:47.458
Hmm.

22:52.000 --> 22:54.208
Thanks for the clam juice,
Wayne.

22:57.500 --> 23:00.166
♪ ♪

23:00.250 --> 23:02.250
[insects trilling]

23:13.416 --> 23:15.416
♪ ♪

23:28.208 --> 23:30.625
Can I go for a hike?
I did all my chores.

23:30.708 --> 23:32.666
Uh...

23:35.083 --> 23:36.583
All right.

23:37.791 --> 23:40.541
- Stick to the trail.
- Okay.

23:42.041 --> 23:44.250
Back before dinner!

23:49.750 --> 23:51.750
♪ ♪

24:09.875 --> 24:12.083
♪ ♪

24:19.583 --> 24:21.583
[Amy] Excuse me.

24:25.166 --> 24:26.750
Uh...

24:28.125 --> 24:29.500
Why are you here?

24:30.541 --> 24:32.666
I don't know.

24:34.208 --> 24:36.750
But I know that
I'm supposed to be here.

24:38.041 --> 24:39.791
Why?

24:44.500 --> 24:46.416
You see that?

24:52.750 --> 24:54.458
I've been...

24:54.541 --> 24:57.375
I've been drawing it
for years and years,

24:57.458 --> 25:01.333
and now... now I see it
all over the place here.

25:03.125 --> 25:05.041
Looks like my family brand.

25:06.708 --> 25:08.500
You're an Abbott?

25:13.458 --> 25:16.083
- Is Royal...
- You know him?

25:22.708 --> 25:24.916
He was acting all weird
this morning,

25:25.000 --> 25:28.125
but I guess
he's always been weird.

25:29.750 --> 25:31.708
Today?

25:32.750 --> 25:34.500
Yeah. At breakfast.

25:34.583 --> 25:36.458
Why?

25:39.666 --> 25:42.208
[softly] Nothing, I'm...

25:42.291 --> 25:45.166
I'm just happy to hear it.

25:47.916 --> 25:50.083
I like your necklace.

25:50.166 --> 25:52.583
Oh. This?

25:52.666 --> 25:54.416
Mm-hmm.

25:54.500 --> 25:56.708
Me, too.

25:58.500 --> 26:00.333
[quietly] Me, too.

26:01.666 --> 26:03.666
♪ ♪

26:18.083 --> 26:20.083
♪ ♪

26:36.416 --> 26:38.625
♪ ♪

26:44.250 --> 26:46.166
[horse snorts]

27:08.041 --> 27:10.041
♪ ♪

27:13.375 --> 27:15.041
[horse snickers]

27:18.708 --> 27:21.250
♪ ♪

27:22.291 --> 27:23.833
[clicks tongue]

27:42.583 --> 27:44.583
♪ ♪

27:52.875 --> 27:55.333
[indistinct conversation]

28:08.916 --> 28:10.541
- [Perry] Potatoes?
- [Cecilia] Mm-hmm.

28:10.583 --> 28:11.958
[spoon banging on dish]

28:12.041 --> 28:13.416
[Cecilia] Thank you.

28:14.916 --> 28:16.833
- Rhett, hand me the bread,
honey.
- [Rhett] Yeah.

28:16.916 --> 28:18.333
Can I pray?

28:20.916 --> 28:22.166
Hmm?

28:22.250 --> 28:24.875
I want to pray for the supper.

28:31.625 --> 28:32.875
All right.

28:34.083 --> 28:35.208
[Royal] Dear God...

28:36.958 --> 28:39.000
...we pray for...

28:41.958 --> 28:44.166
...Trevor.

28:44.250 --> 28:46.333
Mm-hmm.

28:46.416 --> 28:48.583
For his family.

28:51.000 --> 28:52.500
And for our boys.

28:52.583 --> 28:54.875
Our family.

28:57.708 --> 29:01.875
We ask... that You forgive us.

29:04.333 --> 29:06.041
I guess.

29:07.541 --> 29:09.791
We ask that
You show us the way here,

29:09.875 --> 29:11.666
'cause we're in trouble.

29:13.625 --> 29:14.666
We are desperate.

29:16.500 --> 29:17.500
Hmm.

29:19.958 --> 29:22.625
You made this crazy world.

29:24.500 --> 29:26.541
So maybe You can give us
some sort of hint

29:26.625 --> 29:27.916
as to what You're up to,

29:28.000 --> 29:29.916
'cause I don't have
the first fucking clue.

29:32.250 --> 29:33.500
And maybe it's that You have
nothing to do with this,

29:33.583 --> 29:35.583
or maybe You're not even there,
who knows.

29:37.583 --> 29:41.000
There is a big distance
between You and us--

29:41.083 --> 29:44.750
a gap, a void--
there is a great void,

29:44.833 --> 29:46.333
and I'm asking You
to fill that void.

29:46.416 --> 29:48.333
I'm asking You
to fill that void.

29:48.416 --> 29:51.333
I'm asking You to come down here
and explain Yourself,

29:51.416 --> 29:53.458
because this world of Yours
isn't quite adding up,

29:53.541 --> 29:55.041
and I hate You for it,
I really do.

29:55.125 --> 29:57.541
And I don't even think
I fucking believe in You,

29:57.625 --> 30:00.125
but I really hate You.

30:03.041 --> 30:04.750
Hmm.

30:09.750 --> 30:11.625
Amen.

30:16.000 --> 30:17.833
[clock ticking quietly]

30:29.333 --> 30:31.250
- Uh, is there something...
- [door opens]

30:31.333 --> 30:33.041
Sorry I'm late.

30:33.125 --> 30:35.333
- [Perry] Where you been?
- Just out hiking.

30:35.416 --> 30:36.458
I met some hippie woman.

30:36.541 --> 30:38.125
You met some what?

30:38.208 --> 30:39.750
Um, a girl named Autumn.

30:39.833 --> 30:40.875
She knows you.

30:42.083 --> 30:43.458
You stay away from her,
you understand?

30:43.541 --> 30:45.541
- Don't you ever talk
to her again.
- Why?

30:45.625 --> 30:47.750
And that goes for everyone.
No one talks to her.

30:47.833 --> 30:49.541
Got it? No one.

30:53.041 --> 30:54.291
We're moving the cattle.

30:55.333 --> 30:56.375
What?

30:56.458 --> 30:59.208
Moving the cattle
to the east pasture.

30:59.291 --> 31:01.375
- When?
- [Royal] Tomorrow.

31:01.458 --> 31:03.916
They only grazed the west
for a few days.

31:04.000 --> 31:05.916
- It's not time to... Why?
- We're moving them tomorrow.

31:06.000 --> 31:08.541
- 'Cause I say so.
- There's no way we'll find
enough hands in time.

31:08.625 --> 31:11.000
I'm counting ten perfectly
good ones around this table.

31:11.083 --> 31:13.375
- Amy has school.
- Mm-mm. Not tomorrow,
she doesn't.

31:13.458 --> 31:15.250
- Royal...
- No, it's what we're doing,
damn it.

31:15.333 --> 31:17.625
All by ourselves.
We're moving the cattle.

31:19.208 --> 31:20.958
And there is a great void!

31:25.208 --> 31:27.708
We're moving the damn cows
off the west pasture,

31:27.791 --> 31:29.208
and that's that.

31:29.291 --> 31:31.791
Now, pass the goddamn potatoes.

31:31.875 --> 31:34.625
- [♪ The Planters: "My Prayer"]
- ♪ When the twilight is gone ♪

31:34.708 --> 31:37.208
♪ Gone ♪

31:37.291 --> 31:39.916
♪ And those songbirds are
