[indistinct radio chatter]

37:58.458 --> 37:59.833
[man over radio] Once again,
I repeat:

37:59.916 --> 38:02.541
we have movement
inside the wire.

38:02.625 --> 38:04.750
[man continues indistinctly]

38:04.791 --> 38:07.291
Hold your fire. Hold your fire.

38:14.708 --> 38:15.916
Hold.

38:17.875 --> 38:20.250
[indistinct chatter]

38:23.791 --> 38:26.458
♪ ♪

38:54.541 --> 38:56.541
♪ ♪

38:58.541 --> 39:01.333
[man] I say again:
Sector A through manila

39:01.416 --> 39:03.083
Oscar Mike in 20 seconds.

39:03.166 --> 39:04.916
♪ ♪

39:09.625 --> 39:12.166
[man continuing indistinctly]

39:12.250 --> 39:15.458
All teams, teams,
maintain vectors of fire.

39:22.166 --> 39:23.583
This our land?

39:24.625 --> 39:26.041
No.

39:26.125 --> 39:27.916
Not anymore.

39:32.041 --> 39:34.125
Royal.

39:36.166 --> 39:38.125
You died.

39:38.208 --> 39:40.625
You died two years ago.

39:40.708 --> 39:43.125
Okay? You died in my arms.

39:43.208 --> 39:44.916
[gasps]

39:46.083 --> 39:48.625
[man] All teams, take
your positions. We're live,

39:48.708 --> 39:51.625
we're live.
I say again: all teams,

39:51.708 --> 39:54.416
take positions. We're live.
Bravo 5.

39:54.500 --> 39:57.500
[continues indistinctly]

39:57.583 --> 39:59.500
Run.

40:00.625 --> 40:02.666
[♪ The Rolling Stones:
"Paint It, Black"]

40:02.750 --> 40:04.375
♪ ♪

40:04.458 --> 40:07.291
- [woman shrieks]
- [grunts]
- [man] Do not move!

40:07.375 --> 40:12.625
♪ I see a red room,
and I want to paint it black ♪

40:12.708 --> 40:15.000
- ♪ No colors anymore ♪
- [indistinct shouting]

40:15.083 --> 40:18.166
♪ I want them to turn black ♪

40:18.250 --> 40:21.208
♪ I see the girls walk by ♪

40:21.291 --> 40:24.750
♪ Dressed in
their summer clothes ♪

40:24.833 --> 40:27.125
♪ I have to turn my head ♪

40:27.208 --> 40:30.791
♪ Until my darkness goes ♪

40:30.875 --> 40:33.250
♪ I see a line of cars ♪

40:33.333 --> 40:36.541
♪ And they're
all painted black ♪

40:36.625 --> 40:39.250
♪ With flowers and my love ♪

40:39.333 --> 40:42.833
♪ Both never to come back ♪

40:42.916 --> 40:45.375
♪ I've seen people turn
their heads ♪

40:45.458 --> 40:48.791
♪ And quickly look away ♪

40:48.875 --> 40:51.083
♪ Like a newborn baby ♪

40:51.166 --> 40:55.000
♪ It just happens every day ♪

40:55.083 --> 40:57.500
♪ I look inside myself ♪

40:57.583 --> 41:00.666
♪ And see my heart is black ♪

41:00.750 --> 41:03.041
♪ I see my red door ♪

41:03.125 --> 41:07.000
♪ I must have it painted black ♪

41:07.083 --> 41:09.375
♪ Maybe then I'll fade away ♪

41:09.458 --> 41:12.625
♪ And not have to
face the facts ♪

41:12.708 --> 41:15.416
♪ It's not easy facing up ♪

41:15.500 --> 41:19.000
♪ When your whole world
is black ♪

41:19.083 --> 41:21.625
♪ No more will my green sea ♪

41:21.708 --> 41:25.375
♪ Go turn a deeper blue ♪

41:25.458 --> 41:28.291
♪ I could not foresee
this thing ♪

41:28.375 --> 41:31.958
♪ Happening to you ♪

41:32.041 --> 41:34.083
♪ If I look hard enough ♪

41:34.166 --> 41:37.666
♪ Into the setting sun ♪

41:37.750 --> 41:39.916
♪ My love will laugh with me ♪

41:40.000 --> 41:42.750
♪ Before the morning comes ♪

41:42.833 --> 41:46.083
♪ I see a red door ♪

41:46.166 --> 41:49.375
♪ And I want to paint it black ♪

41:50.416 --> 41:52.375
♪ No colors anymore ♪

41:52.458 --> 41:55.250
♪ I want them to turn black ♪

41:56.541 --> 41:58.708
♪ I see the girls walk by ♪

41:58.791 --> 42:02.458
♪ Dressed in
their summer clothes ♪

